Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.78,0:01:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If cases were all men,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.45,0:01:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then I wonder if the unseen puzzles would be women?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.87,0:01:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Chiba has a job for the old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.29,0:01:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A peculiar incident on a dark and stormy night!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.21,0:01:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.92,0:01:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.84,0:01:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Detective Conan ep 666
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Translated by 1412
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,First Draft
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,(Timing: usotsuki)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.44,0:00:05.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Man, what a lazy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.44,0:00:10.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Isn't anyone going to commit a crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.99,0:00:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, don't wish for things like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.65,0:00:16.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll go out drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.66,0:00:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't look like the rain's going to let up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.35,0:00:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's Detective Chiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.42,0:00:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There we go! It's a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.92,0:00:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you have to help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.30,0:00:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I need you to find her, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.35,0:00:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.05,0:00:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to hurry, her life is at stake!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.39,0:02:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing is, I've been seeing this woman since we met in my favorite café.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.60,0:02:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little while ago, she said she wanted to tell me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.87,0:02:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That she felt her life was in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.78,0:02:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Once I get out of jail, first thing I'm gonna do is find you."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.32,0:03:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been sending letters like this for the past year?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.20,0:03:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes... I was scared so I quit my job and moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.83,0:03:11.83,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mio Ashida (23)\NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Mio Ashida (23) Office Worker) (flip the name orders, please)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.29,0:03:11.83,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But even here, I feel like I'm being watched.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.46,0:03:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might be just my imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.51,0:03:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, I told her to let me know right away if she saw him, or if anything escalated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.72,0:03:29.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I left to use the toilet...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.02,0:03:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was suddenly gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.31,0:03:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That woman suddenly paid the bill and left, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.02,0:03:42.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She seemed rather shaken up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.53,0:03:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.03,0:03:45.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:48.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's her umbrella. She must have mistakenly picked up mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't feel like negligence, it felt like he'd tried to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.90,0:04:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had he seen the umbrella and mistaken me for her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.84,0:04:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was stupid of me not to have asked for her address...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought about pursuing this through the office, but there's no definite proof of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.87,0:04:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so I came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.82,0:04:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't sound like much of a case to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.55,0:04:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't know her personal info, so there's not much chance of finding her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you've recently seen her more often at that coffee shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.00,0:04:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,doesn't that mean she's moved closer to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.28,0:04:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we could go to the café, and search outwards from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.18,0:04:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.09,0:04:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, I'm not taking a case like—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.38,0:04:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going, I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,MONTAGE
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:14.50,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is one smart criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,(Murakami Takuya (20) College Applicant) (Rouninsei is a student who failed the entrance exam and is without a school, hence Ronin)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.21,0:05:20.67,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Takuya Murakami (20)\NFailed College Applicant
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.50,0:05:18.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I wish that jerk upstairs would keep it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.95,0:05:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aah, stop! Somebody, help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.05,0:05:29.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a crime in progress?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.26,0:05:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Detective Chiba?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.99,0:05:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes, I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.23,0:05:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A... young woman was involved in a homicide in a nearby flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.95,0:05:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the car from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.71,0:05:49.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are we too late?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.50,0:05:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Chiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:55.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.06,0:05:57.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.91,0:06:00.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't today your day off?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.42,0:06:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She... was killed, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.63,0:06:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hat and sunglasses I saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.23,0:06:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's... not the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.70,0:06:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the assailant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.25,0:06:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.99,0:06:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.78,0:06:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.71,0:06:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.85,0:06:41.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why you came here in search of her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.02,0:06:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.22,0:06:45.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The abandoned car was stolen, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.54,0:06:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.56,0:06:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.59,0:06:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, give us the rundown.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.87,0:06:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.18,0:06:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The incident took place 40 minutes ago, at 9:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.85,0:07:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An unemployed student in the room below, Takuya Murakami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,heard a disturbance and a scream, and came to check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.53,0:07:10.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He found the body and Mio Ashida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} standing next to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.87,0:07:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used his cell phone to contact the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.97,0:07:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the incident, the front door appears to have been unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:21.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The victim is Yoshizumi Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 28.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.21,0:07:25.96,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yoshizumi Karashima (28)\NUnemployed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,(Yoshizumi Karashima (28) Unemployed)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.79,0:07:25.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We've confirmed that he was just released three days ago from traffic jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.49,0:07:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Traffic jail? Was he incarcerated for traffic violations?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.77,0:07:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's correct. One year ago, he was with someone who was driving under the influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.99,0:07:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They ended up breaking the guardrail and falling into a lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two people were thrown from the vehicle,\None died at the scene, one had minor injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.36,0:07:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The driver was at fault, but wasn't prosecuted, due to his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.47,0:07:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The passenger, who was also intoxicated,\Nwas sentenced to one year as an accomplice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:08:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, our victim here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.22,0:08:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother swore he'd never drive again after his first drunk driving offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.56,0:08:12.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Her brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.06,0:08:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karashima was the one driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.60,0:08:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.35,0:08:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased driver was her brother, a Toshiaki Ashida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, he was 28.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.27,0:08:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't believe it when Karashima testified that it had been my brother driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.45,0:08:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I filed several objections, but they were all overruled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.45,0:08:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.20,0:08:41.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A year in prison?! You've gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.21,0:08:44.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is all because of those ridiculous allegations you all brought up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:45.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I won't forget this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:47.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You won't get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.36,0:08:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was just trying to shift the blame!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.84,0:08:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was bitter that he didn't get a suspended sentence. {shift the blame is probably close... sakaurami is "unjustified resentment through misunderstanding"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.84,0:08:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, show them the letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.64,0:08:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.31,0:09:00.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These were all sent while he was incarcerated?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.43,0:09:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They all say, "I'll come pay you a visit the second I'm out of here."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.45,0:09:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A veiled threat, perhaps, but clearly a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.44,0:09:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:14.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's certainly hard to see how else one could interpret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.61,0:09:17.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"I want you to remember, and wait..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.95,0:09:18.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.66,0:09:25.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why's there a gap of almost half a year with no letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably cooled off a bit, then got worked up again once his release drew nearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.27,0:09:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Stupid kids should keep their traps shut!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.30,0:09:36.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you were afraid he was going to be released soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.10,0:09:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you changed jobs and moved here, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.63,0:09:46.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.75,0:09:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just moved here, so that's why most of your appliances and electronics are new.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.36,0:09:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some don't even look like they've been used at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.87,0:09:55.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.81,0:09:57.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They still have price stickers on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.40,0:10:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would generally come home just to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.20,0:10:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.11,0:10:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:08.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Still, everything's a little too neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.38,0:10:13.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Guess she was watching TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:16.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}though not using the remote.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.76,0:10:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please describe how you found the victim after he forced the lock and entered the flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.14,0:10:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I came home, the lights were on,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.30,0:10:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the door was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.94,0:10:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't thinking, and didn't consider he could still be inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.79,0:10:35.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The moment I opened the door, suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.33,0:10:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ashida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fought back using the umbrella she was holding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their struggle took them into the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.05,0:10:56.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So the fatal blow was to the back of the head...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.59,0:11:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, there's a wound on the bridge of his nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.43,0:11:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he was hit during the struggle?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.71,0:11:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, on the edge of the TV stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:14.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It certainly looks like he struck here, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think this is a pretty clear case of self-defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.70,0:11:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems corroborated by the fact that he tried to hit me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.23,0:11:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I took her umbrella by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.37,0:11:30.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:34.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The victim's shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.17,0:11:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, when did the rain start?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.67,0:11:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... It was just as the evening started, so maybe around seven?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.10,0:11:44.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:54.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, if we could get a more detailed statement from you back at the station, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.21,0:11:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.50,0:12:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay, I'll walk you through it. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.63,0:12:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,(Shirt: Pass the Exam) not sure if it's worth translating.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:04.95,Signs,,0,0,0,,Pass the Exam!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.95,0:12:10.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I was telling the detective, I could hear that the TV was on the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.55,0:12:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.65,0:12:17.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm asking for the great detective upstairs, Kogorō Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.21,0:12:20.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when did you first hear the TV turn on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.09,0:12:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From around six o'clock, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.01,0:12:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as it turned off at 9:30, I heard the scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.35,0:12:32.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's sort of a cheap flat, you can hear everything through these paper-thin walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.68,0:12:35.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there any sound other than the TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.46,0:12:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.98,0:12:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wish that jerk upstairs would keep it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.99,0:12:44.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Somebody, help me!{Remove}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.82,0:12:46.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's what it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.83,0:12:49.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.00,0:12:59.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:02.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But that means this case is actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.93,0:13:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now then,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.85,0:13:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, time to go home and have a nice cold beer—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.23,0:13:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.24,0:13:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.82,0:13:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.36,0:13:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, could it be—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.32,0:13:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi. I need you to check on something immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.25,0:13:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.40,0:13:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.77,0:13:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This case hasn't been cracked yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.84,0:13:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes. And when did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.88,0:13:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, this isn't a case of self-defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.55,0:13:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was premeditated murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.09,0:13:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Premeditated murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.76,0:13:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... that's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.30,0:13:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.32,0:14:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take a look at the umbrella stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.92,0:14:04.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It should have a puddle of rainwater at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.43,0:14:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.44,0:14:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The umbrellas we brought are lined up in the entryway,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.19,0:14:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to not contaminate the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means there was only one umbrella in this room:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.09,0:14:23.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Chiba's, which she accidentally took from the café.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.24,0:14:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.72,0:14:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that your umbrella was the one in the stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.10,0:14:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That contradicts her statement that she used it to fight off the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.08,0:14:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who attacked her the moment she entered the flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.63,0:14:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed. She wouldn't have had time to put the umbrella into the stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.31,0:14:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another contradiction as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.20,0:14:50.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the victim drove here in the car parked in the empty lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.03,0:14:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,none of his clothes were even damp.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.76,0:14:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because he must have had an umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.81,0:14:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we just said there couldn't have been another umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.56,0:15:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the victim must have arrived
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.95,0:15:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,before it started raining, before 7 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.47,0:15:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be! He almost ran me over just an hour ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.34,0:15:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, his shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.61,0:15:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's shoes were wet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.97,0:15:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed his shoes are wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.55,0:15:23.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why aren't his socks or pants?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.06,0:15:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.15,0:15:31.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, the victim's possessions include the hat and sunglasses I saw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.36,0:15:35.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we be truly certain that those items actually belonged to the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.73,0:15:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one more inconsistency:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.17,0:15:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the driver seat's setting in that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.45,0:15:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was set to a position far too close for a person with a tall build.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.31,0:15:50.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan confirmed it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.45,0:15:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all circumstantial evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.54,0:15:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it leads us to the same conclusion:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.48,0:16:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,this wasn't self-defense, but a murder planned by Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.94,0:16:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.45,0:16:14.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything went according to Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me start from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.92,0:16:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, she picked the lock to her own front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.54,0:16:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, she called Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.04,0:16:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'll leave it unlocked, so come inside and wait."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.21,0:16:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, she went to the café and told Detective Chiba about the letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.30,0:16:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She made it seem like she was scared and being threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.22,0:16:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She took Detective Chiba's umbrella on purpose, left the restaurant,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.35,0:16:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and attacked Detective Chiba who came after her with her car,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,creating the impression that her life was in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.77,0:16:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had entered the flat earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.95,0:16:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was watching TV while awaiting her return.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:58.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't use the remote, so he turned it on manually.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.41,0:17:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 9:30 PM, Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:05.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} turned off the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.73,0:17:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He faced the TV and pressed the power button.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.59,0:17:10.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was struck from behind with a heavy vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.09,0:17:14.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Falling forward, his nose hit the TV stand, and broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.60,0:17:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the sounds that Murakami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} heard from his room on the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.31,0:17:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She then placed the knife in Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.32,0:17:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and put the hat and sunglasses from her attack on Detective Chiba in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.36,0:17:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the scream that Murakami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.78,0:17:37.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Entirely playacted by Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for him to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.50,0:17:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She likely moved here specifically for the thin walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.50,0:17:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, he also heard the sounds of the actual murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.42,0:17:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that all purely conjecture, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.67,0:17:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, it's at least true that Karashima threatened her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.40,0:17:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's clear from the letters and what he said in the courtroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.00,0:17:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.51,0:18:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right about that day in the courtroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.95,0:18:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what about the letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.31,0:18:10.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially those that were sent after the sudden gap in correspondence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.11,0:18:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along with phrases like "I'll come see you once I get out', we also see many instances of 'I want to meet you so I can tell you the truth."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.20,0:18:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if he intended to confess to her that it really had been him driving on that rainy night one year ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.38,0:18:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.35,0:18:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It certainly seems like a stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.75,0:18:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not just plead guilty at trial or confess to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.79,0:18:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he thought he was running out of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.83,0:18:43.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.27,0:18:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was wondering why there'd been a pause in the letters he'd sent,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.35,0:18:48.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I inquired at the traffic jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.78,0:18:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just before the letters stopped,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a medical exam at the prison infirmary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.85,0:19:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was diagnosed with a terminal illness and given six months to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.57,0:19:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.00,0:19:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, once he was released, he never visited the hospital he was referred to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:14.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was most likely looking for Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who'd quit her job and moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.31,0:19:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he really was trying to confess his crimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.25,0:19:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong, I don't believe you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.41,0:19:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if that were true, I wouldn't forgive him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.22,0:19:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I forgive him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.12,0:19:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After my brother's death, I broke off my engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.48,0:19:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father put off retirement, and overworked himself until he fell ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.90,0:19:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both he and my mother passed away,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.31,0:19:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,nobody would help us, and there was nothing I could do but watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.22,0:19:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one believed my brother was innocent. That's why—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.53,0:19:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,—you decided to take revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.97,0:19:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you... admitting you did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.78,0:19:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.85,0:20:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to steal the show from the great detective, who only found circumstantial evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.16,0:20:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't regret what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.51,0:20:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not one bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.97,0:20:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.40,0:20:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then let me show you the truth that I found, rather than circumstantial evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.45,0:20:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps once you see it, you'll realize that you've committed a meaningless murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.13,0:20:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I don't believe there is such a thing as a justifiable murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.60,0:20:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.51,0:20:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recreating the scene'll be easier than explaining it. Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.55,0:20:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.92,0:20:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss, you can be Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.55,0:20:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Detective Chiba can play her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.35,0:20:40.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure, can you turn on the TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.56,0:20:41.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.44,0:20:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now Chiba, pretend to swing the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.06,0:20:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.48,0:20:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, from that position, please turn off the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.24,0:20:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.98,0:21:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karashima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw you standing behind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.70,0:21:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet, he didn't run.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.95,0:21:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What he'd wanted all along was to beg for\Nforgiveness, and put himself at your mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.31,0:21:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes... he'd come to regret what he did,\Nfrom the bottom of his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.63,0:21:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing that, can you still have no regrets?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,ENDING SONG DAKARA BABY BABY
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.64,0:22:54.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This case was the final chapter of an accident that happened one year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.31,0:22:58.10,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the lives that were lost will never return.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.60,0:23:00.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nor will guilt be easily erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.35,0:23:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, I couldn't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.69,0:23:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.12,0:23:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't blame yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.16,0:23:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I involved you to give the police a chance to redeem themselves for their mistake a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.55,0:23:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I had found you earlier, and given you the umbrella...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.20,0:23:27.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...perhaps I could have kept you from\Ncommitting a murder, at least for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.42,0:23:32.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, I don't have the right\Nto let you hold an umbrella over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.18,0:23:34.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.86,0:23:36.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.68,0:23:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.20,0:23:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose now it's her turn to atone for her crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.90,0:23:49.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think at least Detective Chiba was able to express his feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.95,0:23:54.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm sure you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.26,0:24:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even if you congratulate us...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.59,0:24:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you, Hatsune?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.60,0:24:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She hired me...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.85,0:24:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...as a private eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.49,0:24:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.06,0:24:19.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A... detective?
